 Rosevear and are typically due in March for the following summer.   Free; a stipend is awarded to participants','Susan Rosevear','CMSE','77 Massachusetts Ave., Room 13-2082\nCambridge, MA 02139','617-253-0916','volunteerplacement@mit.edu','Kristi Gundrum Kebinger','Public Service Center','77 Massachusetts Ave, 4-104\nCambridge, MA 02139','617-253-0742','kristig@MIT.EDU','Susan Rosevear','77 Massachusetts Ave., Room 13-2082\nCambridge, MA 02139','617-253-0916','volunteerplacement@mit.edu','','','','','http://mit.edu/cmse/educational/research.html','48.jpg','48.jpg.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07',6,'0','0','0','0','0','0','Center for Materials Science and Engineering',NULL,'2010-04-07','0','','CMSE','2010-04-07','2010-04-07',NULL,NULL),(39,'Adopt-a-boat','The Adopt-a-Boat program facilitates educational partnerships between fishermen and K-12 classrooms throughout New England. Teachers/classrooms and fishermen work together to create a partnership that fits their individual classroom goals. By partnering with classrooms, fishermen help educate students about marine ecology, the complexities of marine resource utilization, and the daily life of fishermen. Conceptualized and organized by New England fishermen, the MIT Sea Grant College Program and other cooperating organization, Adopt-a-Boat works to present a balanced picture of commercial fishing, thereby building a citizenry enlightened about marine resources and the importance of coastal communities. Partnerships have included classroom visits by fishermen, overnight trips on fishing vessels, tours of vessels, and introductions to fishing gear and equipment.','The Adopt-a-Boat program facilitates educational partnerships between fishermen and K-12 classrooms throughout New England.','Please contact the program coordinator to set up your partnership today. Partnerships can last for one visit, several months, or the whole year. The Adopt-a-Boat staff is available for guidance, but each partnership is worked out between the teacher and his/her fishermen. Previous partnerships have been with vessels in the same geographic region or hundreds of miles away. The choice is yours.','Sarah Olivo','MIT Sea Grant','3 Cambridge Center\nCambridge, MA 02142','617-715-5148','volunteerplacement@mit.edu','Kristi Gundrum Kebinger','Public Service Center','77 Massachusetts Avenue, 4-104\nCambridge, MA 02139','617-253-0742','kristig@MIT.EDU','Sarah Olivo','3 Cambridge Center\nCambridge, MA 02142','617-715-5148','volunteerplacement@mit.edu','','','','','http://www.adoptaboat.org/','62.jpg','62.jpg.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-04-07','2010-06-18','2010-04-07','2010-04-07',6,'0','0','0','0','0','0','MIT Sea Grant',NULL,'2010-04-07','0','','MIT Sea Grant','2010-04-07','2010-04-07',NULL,NULL),(40,'Haystack Observatory Classroom Tours','MIT Haystack Observatory in Westford, MA, offers tours to middle school and high school teachers and students throughout the year. Each tour consists of a short lecture on radio astronomy or atmospheric science by one of Haystack\'s research scientists, followed by a tour of one of the Observatory\'s facilities. Total time is approximately one hour. Before 